body.description: Add a touch of color to your kitchen with the vibrant style of the GreenPan Rio collection. This 12" frypan is designed to make your meals better. How? This pan features our Thermolon healthy ceramic nonstick coating—an easy release and wipe clean coating that’s free of PFAS, PFOA, lead, and cadmium for worry-free cooking. Unlike many other nonstick coatings, it will never release toxic fumes, even if it’s overheated. This durable coating is reinforced with diamonds to provide peak nonstick performance longer. The pan's heavy-duty construction gives you even heat distribution while the stay-cool Bakelite handle gives you a comfortable grip and total control. Dishwasher safe. Oven safe to 350°F..

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great non stick pan
reviews.reviewText: Been using this pan for 5 weeks, and it’s great. Heat’s well, great non-stick, and easy to clean. I even cut food on it with a metal steak knife and no damage at all. The sidewalls are not high, so that’s the only critique I’d mention. But overall, a great fry pan for the money. I use the glass lid from my prior pan, so I do recommend a lid as well. Good luck. Mark in NY

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love the pan, easy to wash, defiantly nonstick, works great, very stylish

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Received this today, tried it out
reviews.reviewText: Gave it a light cleaning, a spoonful of vegetable oil and proceeded to make 5 lbs of meatballs and a pack of sausage over medium heat. Took at least an hour. You would have thought those meatballs were in the NHL… they slid all over, by the second batch they were browning nicely. At the end I poured all of the grease into a bowl to cool and wiped it with a paper towel and it was almost completely clean… another gentle washing and it’s dried and ready for the next time. If anything changes in the future I’ll update this but it looks like it’s gonna be a great pan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is an excellent fry skillet. Used it to make pancakes and it performed better than expected. Heat distribution was great which made for perfect pancakes, and it cleaned very easily with just hot water and a little soap on a sponge. Just following the directions on the sticker for use an care will help this skillet to last for a long time. But it was an ordeal trying to get it.After ordering it and a few days later receiving notification that it was delivered, went to the door and it wasn't there. After waiting 24 hours based on instructions from Amazon, it still didn't show up. So asked and was granted a refund while putting in an order again for the skillet. A few days later, it showed up (this time) at the door but upon unpacking it was found to be smashed on one side. So contacted Amazon, ordered a replacement, and then returned the damaged skillet via Amazon returns with Kohl's. The replacement was delivered to our door the other day in good condition and as stated above, performed admirably, hence the 5-star rating which also covers Amazon's customer service. As for the shipping debacle...which was on the postal service...3 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Functions and cleans up easily, but....
reviews.reviewText: The pan arrived with a small warp on one edge. It cooks very well and cleans up easily. However, the porcelain surface inside the pan is very fragile. The smallest lightest touch to the surface causes nicks to form. Not sure how long the pan will actually hold up. There are several nicks on the inside with careful and light use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Bought 10/09/2023 and ineffective by January 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this pan as a recommendation from a coworker- the Amazon reviews did not sway my decision. We needed a new nonstick pan to replace our last one that we had for 3 years.We bought this pan on October 9, 2023 and we use it for scrambled eggs on weekday mornings. We do not use a metal spatula, just a rubber one. Also, I hand wash my dishes and do not typically run the dishwasher.I noticed about a month after using the pan, little flakes of the nonstick coating had come off the surface to reveal the black underneath but there were only like 2 or 3 small chips so I didn’t care too much. I did also notice that it was getting food stuck to it more and more but thought that was just normal.Today 01/29/024 my boyfriend uses the pans for eggs and he just finished cooking and he sounds very frustrated and mentions how the nonstick coating of the pan didn’t last long and shows me the pan with a bunch of egg still stuck to it.The pan worked well for maybe a month. But three months later it’s not great. I would return it but the return window is over. Oh well. I will buy a different pan I guess.
